{
  "texts": [
    "(van Benthem 1981 considers taking only the finitely axiomatized consistent sets.)",
    "As he remarks: \"There is something inelegant to an ordinary Henkin argument.",
    "One has a consistent set of sentences S, perhaps quite small, that one would like to see satisfied semantically.",
    "Now, some arbitrary maximal extensions S + of S is to be taken to obtain a model (for S +, and hence for S)-but the added part S + -S plays no role subsequently.",
    "We started out with something partial, but the method forces us to be total\" [1988, p. 78]."
  ]
}